Can do the further check by
1. Adding `is_train=False` to module `bind` function;
2. Using NaiveEngine for prediction-only jobs;
3. Adding mxnet profiler to get detailed profiling results from backend. https://mxnet.incubator.apache.org/how_to/perf.html#profiler
Thanks.

@piiswrong, its a bit tricky because in kvstore.cc, the creation of kvstore_dist_server requires the template argument which specifies in this what dtype to use. 

If we refactor the classes such that there is a class DistServerWrapper (with better name of course) which receives message from worker with dtype and then creates the DistServer, then it can work I think. The wrapper only needs to perform this receiving of commands I think. Everything else can be in dist_server. 

@solin319 I'm not sure if the current way of ```mx.kvstore_server._init_kvstore_server_module(args.dtype)``` is a good interface. What do others think? The above might work

